
This is a must attend if you will be conducting a job search during fall 01 
and spring 02.
If you are within 1yr. of graduating and want to participate in the
?On-Campus-Recruiting program you will need to know this information.
EveMBA Job placement and salary information for evening students will be 
available via BearTracks this training session will show you how to log-on 
and access the EveMBA salary information.



Tues. 4/24 & Wed. 4/25 BearTracks training at 7:30 P.M. Career Center 
Conference room S420.

BearTracks is the gateway to gaining information on: Company presentations, 
gathering hiring manager contact data for a proactive jobsearch, posting your 
resume and bidding on interviews with companies conducting 
On-Campus-Recruiting (this option can only be exercised when you are within 
12 mos. of graduating), exploring internship opportunities, recording job 
placement data while in the EveMBA program and placement data upon 
graduation, plus you will be able to access aggregate salary placement data 
unique to EveMBA students.? Make sure and attend this training, it will give 
you a head start for all of the fall career related activities.

WHERE:? Career Center Conference room S420

